  "transcript": "Have you ever noticed that ChatGPT is pretty much just a yes, man? No matter what you ask it, it'll say you're smart. That's a great idea. But that's because behind the language model is actually a system prompt that the engineering team designed for it to respond in that way, making it agreeable and trying to solve whatever question you ask it for a better user experience. But it might not actually help you improve. The right way is to actually give it the instructions to do so. So here's what I want you to do. Go into the instructions and then go to default instructions and write this in there. Be my ruthless mentor. If my ideas are bad, tell me why. You need to stress test everything and get things to the point where it's bulletproof. So just comment bulletproof, and I'll send you the other prompts.",
